The operator reported that prior to the accident flight the pilot was distracted during a 
refueling operation. The distraction involved ground personnel entering the helicopter cabin 
after landing to discuss the next spraying operation with the pilot. After the conversation, the 
pilot departed without refueling the helicopter. While completing an aerial application, the 
engine experienced a loss of engine power. The pilot initiated an autorotation, during which 
the helicopter impacted terrain. A postaccident examination of the helicopter revealed the tail 
boom was partially separated and the landing gear skids were bent. The operator reported that 
approximately 3.5 quarts of fuel were drained from the fuel tanks, and 2 gallons of fuel were 
considered unusable.
The pilot's failure to refuel the helicopter which resulted in a loss of engine power due to fuel 
exhaustion.
